HALLET CAREY SWART, Ltd., Libelant-Appellee, v. THE Steamer W. C. FRANZ, Her Engines, etc., The Algoma Central & Hudson Bay Railway Co., Claimant-Appellant. No. 83. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Dec. 4, 1933. Brown, Ely & Richards, of Buffalo, N. Y. (Laurence E. Coffey, of Buffald, N. Y., of counsel), for appellant. Bigham, Englar, Jones & Houston, of New York City, and Burke & Desmond, of Buffalo, N. Y. (Henry N. Longley, Thomas C. Burke, and Ezra G. Benedict Fox, all of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (2 F. Supp. 497) affirmed.
